# CourtIQ — production runbook

Copy once: `cp DEPLOY.local.md.example DEPLOY.local.md`  
`DEPLOY.local.md` is gitignored (your URLs stay private).

---

# FIRST-TIME SETUP

## 1. GCP VM

1. [GCP Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/) → Compute Engine → **Create instance**
2. **Name:** `courtiq-instance` · **Machine:** e2-micro · **Region:** `us-central1`
3. **Boot disk:** Ubuntu 22.04, 30 GB
4. **Network tags:** `courtiq` → Create

**Firewall** (once):

```bash
gcloud compute firewall-rules create courtiq-api \
  --allow=tcp:8080,tcp:8000 \
  --target-tags=courtiq
```

**VM external IP** → GCP → VM instances → **External IP** (for SSH + GitHub `VM_HOST`).

---

## 2. VM — Docker + backend

SSH in: `ssh YOUR_USER@YOUR_VM_IP`

```bash
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y docker.io docker-compose-v2 git curl

# 1 GB RAM — add swap before first build
sudo fallocate -l 2G /swapfile && sudo chmod 600 /swapfile
sudo mkswap /swapfile && sudo swapon /swapfile

sudo usermod -aG docker "$USER"
# log out and SSH back in

git clone https://github.com/Warsame-Egal/court-iq.git
cd court-iq
cp .env.production.example .env
```

Edit `.env` after tunnels (step 3). For now, build:

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build
```

Check (~2 min on e2-micro):

```bash
curl -s http://localhost:8080/actuator/health
curl -s http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health
```

---

## 3. Cloudflare tunnels — background (`nohup`)

Install [cloudflared](https://developers.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-one/connections/connect-networks/downloads/) on the VM.

**Start both tunnels** (survives SSH logout):

```bash
pkill cloudflared 2>/dev/null || true

nohup cloudflared tunnel --url http://localhost:8080 > ~/cf-spring.log 2>&1 &
nohup cloudflared tunnel --url http://localhost:8000 > ~/cf-fastapi.log 2>&1 &
```

**Get URLs** (~10 sec):

```bash
grep -o 'https://[^ ]*trycloudflare.com' ~/cf-spring.log    # Spring → .env + Vercel API
grep -o 'https://[^ ]*trycloudflare.com' ~/cf-fastapi.log   # FastAPI → Vercel WS host only
pgrep -a cloudflared   # should show 2 processes
```

| Tunnel | Port | Goes where |
|--------|------|------------|
| `cf-spring.log` | 8080 | VM `.env` → `SERVER_URL` (full `https://…`) |
| `cf-fastapi.log` | 8000 | Vercel → `VITE_WS_URL` (**hostname only**, no `https://`) |

**Update VM `.env`:**

```bash
nano ~/court-iq/.env
```

```env
SERVER_URL=https://YOUR-SPRING-TUNNEL.trycloudflare.com
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://court-iq-alpha.vercel.app
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://court-iq-alpha.vercel.app
NBA_API_PROXY=http://USER:PASS@HOST:PORT
```

No `FASTAPI_BASE_URL` line.

```bash
cd ~/court-iq
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d springboot
```

**Test from Windows CMD** (not from inside the VM):

```cmd
curl.exe "https://YOUR-SPRING-TUNNEL.trycloudflare.com/actuator/health"
```

---

## 4. Vercel frontend

1. [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) → Import repo → **Root Directory:** `frontend`
2. **Settings → Environment Variables** (Production):

| Name | Value |
|------|--------|
| `VITE_API_BASE_URL` | Same as `SERVER_URL` |
| `VITE_WS_URL` | FastAPI tunnel hostname only (e.g. `something.trycloudflare.com`) |

3. Deploy → https://court-iq-alpha.vercel.app

---

## 5. GitHub Actions auto-deploy (Windows CMD, one-time)

Repo → **Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → Repository secrets**

### A. Create deploy key (any folder in CMD)

```cmd
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -f C:\Users\Warsa\courtiq-deploy -N ""
```

### B. Public key → VM

```cmd
type C:\Users\Warsa\courtiq-deploy.pub
```

Copy the one line → on VM:

```bash
nano ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
# paste line at end, save
chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
```

### C. Three GitHub secrets

| Secret name | How to get value | Example |
|-------------|------------------|---------|
| `VM_HOST` | GCP → VM **External IP** or on VM: `curl -s ifconfig.me` | `35.238.67.7` |
| `VM_USER` | On VM: `whoami` or name before `@` when you SSH | `warsameegal0` |
| `VM_SSH_KEY` | **Private** key — CMD: `notepad C:\Users\Warsa\courtiq-deploy` → Ctrl+A, Ctrl+C. Must include `-----BEGIN` through `-----END`. **Not** the `.pub` file. | (multiline key) |

**Verify key file (CMD):**

```cmd
ssh-keygen -y -f C:\Users\Warsa\courtiq-deploy
type C:\Users\Warsa\courtiq-deploy.pub
```

First command should print `ssh-ed25519 …`. Second is **public only** (for VM, not GitHub).

**Test SSH (CMD):**

```cmd
ssh -i C:\Users\Warsa\courtiq-deploy warsameegal0@35.238.67.7 "echo ok"
```

Must print `ok`. Then **Actions → CI → Re-run** or push to `main`.

---

# EVERY DAY — SHIP CODE

On your laptop:

```cmd
git add .
git commit -m "your message"
git push
```

| What | What happens |
|------|----------------|
| **Vercel** | Auto-builds frontend on every `main` push |
| **GCP VM** | CI tests pass → SSH runs `scripts/deploy.sh` when backend files changed |
| **You** | Nothing else unless tunnels died or you changed `.env` |

Optional manual deploy on VM: `bash ~/court-iq/scripts/deploy.sh`

---

# WHEN TUNNELS RESTART (VM reboot, `pkill`, etc.)

Quick tunnels get **new URLs** each time. Same `nohup` commands:

```bash
pkill cloudflared 2>/dev/null || true
nohup cloudflared tunnel --url http://localhost:8080 > ~/cf-spring.log 2>&1 &
nohup cloudflared tunnel --url http://localhost:8000 > ~/cf-fastapi.log 2>&1 &
grep -o 'https://[^ ]*trycloudflare.com' ~/cf-spring.log
grep -o 'https://[^ ]*trycloudflare.com' ~/cf-fastapi.log
```

1. Update `SERVER_URL` in `~/court-iq/.env`
2. `docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d springboot`
3. Vercel → update `VITE_API_BASE_URL` + `VITE_WS_URL` → **Redeploy**
4. Update the table below in `DEPLOY.local.md`

**Logs:** `tail -f ~/cf-spring.log` · **Stop tunnels:** `pkill cloudflared`

---

# MY URLS (update when tunnels change)

| What | Value |
|------|--------|
| VM IP (`VM_HOST`) | |
| VM user (`VM_USER`) | |
| Spring tunnel (`SERVER_URL` / `VITE_API_BASE_URL`) | `https://` |
| FastAPI WS host (`VITE_WS_URL`, no https) | |
| Vercel app | `https://court-iq-alpha.vercel.app` |

---

# QUICK CHECKS

| Check | Command |
|-------|---------|
| Tunnels running | `pgrep -a cloudflared` (2 lines) |
| Spring on VM | `curl -s http://localhost:8080/actuator/health` |
| FastAPI on VM | `curl -s http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health` |
| Spring via tunnel | `curl.exe https://YOUR-SPRING-TUNNEL.../actuator/health` (Windows) |
| GitHub deploy | Actions → CI → **deploy** step green |
